cs.DB, cs.CR, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.IT. 

The paper proposes an anonymization technique for databases, which suggests that it could belong to the cs.DB (Databases) category. The technique aims to release the least possible amount of information while preserving the utility of the data, which could fall under the cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) category. The use of Principal Component Analysis suggests that it could also belong to the cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) category. The proposed metrics for assessing utility are based on matrix norms, correlation coefficients, divergence measures, and quality indices of database images, which could fall under the cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.IT (Information Theory) categories.
